Characterization and Dynamic Shift of Microbial Communities during Start - Up, Overloading and Steady - State in an Anaerobic Membrane Bioreactor A lab - scale anaerobic membrane bioreactor ( AnMBR) with a side stream tubular membrane was developed to treat synthetic domestic sewage to evaluate its performance and the dynamic shift of bacterial and archaeal communities during the start - up, steady - state, overloading and recovery periods of operation at mesophilic temperatures.
